**Missed Issues**
- The audit missed a real rollout-policy behavior gap. `isFeatureEnabled()` returns `true` for partial rollouts when `identity` is missing, and most `search-flags.ts` wrappers call it without identity. That conflicts with duplicated docs that describe `SPECKIT_ROLLOUT_PERCENT` as a global gate on individual flags. This is material because it changes effective behavior for many governance-related flags, not just wording. Evidence: [rollout-policy.ts:41](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts#L41) [rollout-policy.ts:45](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/cognitive/rollout-policy.ts#L45) [search-flags.ts:16](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts#L16) [search-flags.ts:141](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts#L141) [search-flags.ts:197](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts#L197) [search-flags.ts:207](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/search-flags.ts#L207) [feature-flag-reference.md:72](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/20--feature-flag-reference/01-1-search-pipeline-features-speckit.md#L72) [mcp_server/README.md:736](/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Opencode%20Env/Public/.opencode/skill/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md#L736)
